branch ruleset:
* any changes that comes to that branch it should have pull request before merging 
*when the changes have been made to the file that is already been reveiwed and approved(stale) again it should be approved
*before merging the code owner should approved that file
*the files should have approval of someone other than one who is pushing
* the file should cleared the review history meaning the previous reveiws should cleared
* only github verified users can push 
* the commit history should be linear to that particular file
* we can define branch rules to disable force pushing
* can make the branch as read only by locking the branch
* the users in the bypassing list shouls also follow the above ruleset 